Event category groups event types related to a common object such as a process, file, driver, task, indicator, IP. For example, filtering on event.category = 'process' yields all events relating to process activity.
Unique SentinelOne identifier for the event
Count of Concurrent Identical Events
The time the event was created. Format: epoch time (milliseconds since 1.1.1970), Timezone: UTC

Type of operating system, application, network or user activity observed by the agent on the endpoint. Event types can include for example: Process events such as process creation or process termination Memory events such as memory read or write Driver events such as driver creation Registry events such as registry key renaming File events such as file creation, modification or deletion Network events such as IP connect, DNS resolved or URL Post Profile events such as Profile addition or removal. Event types are categorized to different groups by event.category
